.TH AUTOTERM 1 "November 2025" "AutoTerm 1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
autoterm \- AI-powered terminal command assistant
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B autoterm-backend
[\fB\-\-setup\fR] [\fB\-\-test\fR] [\fB\-\-version\fR] [\fIQUERY\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B AutoTerm
is an AI-powered terminal assistant that translates natural language queries into executable shell commands. It integrates seamlessly with zsh, providing instant command suggestions with context awareness.
.PP
AutoTerm uses Groq's ultra-fast AI models to generate commands based on your natural language input. It maintains conversation context throughout your session, allowing for iterative refinement and complex multi-step command generation.
.SH USAGE
In your terminal, type a query starting with
.B #
followed by your request in natural language, then press
.B Tab
twice to generate a command.
.PP
.B Example:
.PP
.RS
# find all python files modified today
.RE
.PP
Press
.B Tab Tab
to generate:
.PP
.RS
find . -name "*.py" -type f -mtime 0
.RE
.SH KEY BINDINGS
.TP
.B Tab Tab
Generate command from query (when line starts with #)
.TP
.B Enter
Execute the suggested command
.TP
.B Escape
Cancel and return to normal prompt
.TP
.B Tab
(after suggestion) Show conversation history and refine query
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B # clear
Clear conversation context and start fresh
.TP
.B # reset
Same as "# clear"
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-setup
Configure Groq API key
.TP
.B \-\-test
Test connection to Groq API
.TP
.B \-\-version
Display version information
.TP
.B \-\-context \fIJSON\fR
Provide conversation context as JSON (used internally)
.SH CONTEXT PERSISTENCE
AutoTerm maintains conversation context throughout your terminal session. Each new query automatically includes information from previous queries and commands, allowing the AI to understand refinements like "sort by size" or "only in src directory".
.PP
The context persists until you:
.IP \(bu 2
Type
.B # clear
or
.B # reset
.IP \(bu 2
Press
.B Escape
to cancel a command
.IP \(bu 2
Close your terminal session
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/autoterm/config.json
Configuration file containing API key (permissions: 600)
.TP
.I ~/.config/autoterm/history.json
Command generation history (last 10 entries)
.TP
.I ~/.zshrc
Shell configuration file where AutoTerm is sourced
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B GROQ_API_KEY
Groq API key (overrides config file)
.TP
.B AUTOTERM_PREFIX
Custom installation prefix for AutoTerm files
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
